    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doors that are attached, usually on one side or the top, by metal hinges, allowing the door to pivot open. The hinges typically allow the door to open away from the doorway in one direction but not in the other on a vertical or horizontal axis of rotation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>使用金屬鉸鏈連接一側或頂部的門，以利門旋轉開合。鉸鏈可讓門單向從門口打開，而不能從另一方向沿著橫向或縱向的旋轉軸打開。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
